    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200\u00b0C/ 180\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Take a generous knob of <strong>butter </strong>out of the fridge and set aside to soften</p><p>Add your <strong>pigs in blankets</strong> to a baking tray and put in the oven for an initial 5-7 min</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/hot-honey-baked-camembert-and-pigs-in-blankets-festive-picky-tea/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Unwrap your <strong>camembert[s]</strong> and score a criss-cross pattern in the top using a sharp knife</p><p>Add a piece of <strong>tin foil</strong>, large enough to cover the base and sides with some overhang, into a small <strong>oven-proof dish </strong>and top with a similar sized piece of <strong>baking paper</strong></p><p>Top with the <strong>scored camembert[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/hot-honey-baked-camembert-and-pigs-in-blankets-festive-picky-tea/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>camembert[s] dish</strong> to the other side of the baking tray with the pigs in blankets and put in the oven for a further 12-15 min or until the camembert is melted and the pigs in blankets are golden brown and cooked through (no pink meat!)</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4 or more? Use a separate baking tray for your camembert!</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/hot-honey-baked-camembert-and-pigs-in-blankets-festive-picky-tea/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Top, tail, peel and chop your <strong>carrot[s]</strong> into batons</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/hot-honey-baked-camembert-and-pigs-in-blankets-festive-picky-tea/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Deseed your <strong>pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/hot-honey-baked-camembert-and-pigs-in-blankets-festive-picky-tea/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the camembert is melted, remove the tray from the oven and top with your <strong>honey</strong> and <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p><p>Return the tray to the oven for a final 2-3 min or until bubbling \u2013 this is your <strong>hot honey baked camembert</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/hot-honey-baked-camembert-and-pigs-in-blankets-festive-picky-tea/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst everything is cooking, slice your <strong>ciabatta[s]</strong> in half and place in the <strong>toaster</strong> for 1-2 min or until toasted</p><p>Peel your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Rub the toasted ciabatta with the <strong>peeled garlic</strong>, then spread with the <strong>softened butter </strong>and cut into triangles \u2013 this is your <strong>garlic butter ciabatta</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/hot-honey-baked-camembert-and-pigs-in-blankets-festive-picky-tea/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>cranberry sauce</strong> to a small pot</p><p>Serve the <strong>hot honey baked camembert</strong> in the centre of a board</p><p>Arrange the <strong>garlic butter ciabatta</strong>, <strong>carrot batons</strong>, <strong>pepper strips</strong>, <strong>pigs in blankets</strong>, <strong>cranberry sauce</strong> and your <strong>sliced prosciutto</strong> around it</p><p>Dig in!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
